        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-04-26T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-04-26T17:00:00-05:00" n="625" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d625">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50 Recovery/4–2649: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Canton</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ludden</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-26T18:00:00-04:00">April 26, 1949—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>178. For Merchant from Butterworth. You should know ECA is diverting cotton
                    shipments from Shanghai and in process moving headquarters Canton-Hong Kong. If
                    further large expenditures Shanghai can in fact be obviated there wld be
                    substantial increase in sums available Formosa and other projects.
                    [Butterworth.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
